Fairfax Financial, Lundin Mining, Onex: Canadian Equity Preview

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   T a y l o r   a n d   M a t t   W a l c o f f
-- 
2011-08-02T12:43:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/centerra-gold-catalyst-paper-lundin-canadian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Canadian trading.  Barrick Gold Corp. (ABX)   and  Kinross Gold Corp. (K)  :
The gold producers said their Cerro Casale gold project in Chile
will cost $5.2 billion to develop.  Centerra Gold Inc. (CG)  : The mining company with
operations in Kyrgyzstan and Mongolia was cut to “neutral”
from “overweight” by Sabrina Grandchamps, an analyst at HSBC
Securities USA Inc.  Catalyst Paper Corp. (CTL)  : The papermaker reported a
second-quarter loss excluding some items of 12 Canadian cents a
share, wider than the average estimate of analysts surveyed by
Bloomberg of a loss of 8 Canadian cents a share.  Fairfax Financial Holdings Ltd. (FFH)  : The insurer had
its rating raised to “buy” from “market perform” by Jeff Fenwick, an analyst at Cormark Securities Inc.  Lundin Mining Corp. (LUN)  : The base-metals producer
reported second quarter earnings excluding some items that
missed the average analyst estimate by 20 percent, Bloomberg
data show.  Onex Corp. (OCX)  : The private equity firm said it
amended its previous agreement to invest in Jeld-Wen Holding
Inc., boosting amount to $864 million from $675 million.  Talisman Energy Inc. (TLM)  : The oil and gas producer
with operations in  North America , the North Sea and Indonesia
had its rating raised to “market perform” from
“underperform” by Bob Brackett, an analyst at
AllianceBernstein Holding LP.  To contact the reporters on this story:
